  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger </strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>cauliflower</strong> into 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span> wedges</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>coconut yoghurt</strong>,<strong> chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>ground turmeric</strong> and <strong>curry powder</strong> in a large bowl</p>\n<p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> – this is your <strong>tandoori marinade</strong></p>\n<p>Using clean hands, add the <strong>cauliflower wedges</strong> to the <strong>tandoori marinade</strong> and give it a good mix up until fully covered in marinade</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>marinated cauliflower</strong> to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until cooked through and browned</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse the <strong>can</strong><strong><strong>ned</strong> lentils</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> basmati rice</strong>, <strong>sultanas</strong> and 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml] </span><strong>cold water </strong>to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\n<p>Once cooked, add the <strong>drained lentils</strong>, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving – this is your <strong>sultana and lentil rice</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and roughly chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks </p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Grind the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>in a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>until you're left with a smooth paste</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!) a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>water</strong> to the paste and mix to combine – this is your <strong>coriander chutney </strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> cauliflower</strong> is cooked, add the<strong> flaked almonds </strong>to the tray</p>\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for 2-3 min or until toasted </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/tandoori-cauli-rice-and-coriander-chutney/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> tandoori cauliflower</strong> over the <strong>sultana and lentil rice</strong></p>\n<p>Drizzle with the <strong>coriander chutney</strong> and garnish with the <strong>flaked almonds</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy! </p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
